post_cb({"5641925": {"ParentId": "5641805", "CommentCount": "1", "Body": "<p>The type of the expression controlling the <code>switch</code> controls they type of the expression the <code>case</code> labels will use.</p>\n<p>You'll need an <code>__int64</code> (or equivalent) type in the controlling expression to get rid of the warning.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "12711", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "5641925", "Score": "5", "CreationDate": "2011-04-12T21:37:08.847", "LastActivityDate": "2011-04-12T21:37:08.847"}, "5641928": {"ParentId": "5641805", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2011-04-12T21:37:25.593", "Score": "3", "LastEditorUserId": "25324", "LastEditDate": "2011-04-12T21:47:48.503", "Id": "5641928", "OwnerUserId": "25324", "Body": "<p>The C Standard (<a href=\"http://www.open-std.org/JTC1/sc22/wg14/www/docs/n1256.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">n1256.pdf</a>) states</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_5641805_5641928_0\">6.8.4.2/5 The integer promotions are performed on the controlling expression. ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>and </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_5641805_5641928_1\">6.3.1.1/2 ... the value is converted to an int; otherwise, it is converted to an unsigned int ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>My guess is that <code>int</code> (or <code>unsigned int</code>) in your implementation is not large enough to hold 64-bit-wide values.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2011-04-12T21:47:48.503"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_5641805_5641928_1": {"section_id": 21, "quality": 0.75, "length": 6}}, "n3337": {"so_5641805_5641928_1": {"section_id": 18, "quality": 0.75, "length": 6}}, "n4659": {"so_5641805_5641928_1": {"section_id": 21, "quality": 0.75, "length": 6}, "so_5641805_5641928_0": {"section_id": 7569, "quality": 0.5714285714285714, "length": 4}}}, "5641805": {"CommentCount": "8", "AcceptedAnswerId": "5641925", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "572586", "CreationDate": "2011-04-12T21:23:51.910", "LastActivityDate": "2011-04-13T05:23:58.403", "LastEditDate": "2011-04-13T05:23:58.403", "ViewCount": "196", "FavoriteCount": "1", "Title": "Why do I receive a warning for1I64<<31?", "Id": "5641805", "Score": "2", "Body": "<p>Why do I receive a warning for this code ?</p>\n<pre><code>switch(iInput)\n{\n   ...\n   case 1I64&lt;&lt;31:   return 31;  break;\n   ...\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>1&gt;C:\\path-to-file.cpp(44) : warning C4309: 'case' : truncation of constant value</p>\n<p>1I64&lt;&lt;31 is 0x0000000080000000  (__int64) so no truncation here, \nit's there a maximum value for case ?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c>", "OwnerUserId": "572586", "AnswerCount": "2"}});